1
00:00:04,537 --> 00:00:05,638
<i>I decided</i>

2
00:00:05,705 --> 00:00:07,207
<i>to close this office.</i>

3
00:00:07,273 --> 00:00:10,443
So I want you to go to Fukushi's place.

4
00:00:10,510 --> 00:00:12,445
I don't agree with you, but I'll comply.

5
00:00:12,512 --> 00:00:15,749
<i>I have information that will</i>
<i>overthrow Jidori.</i>

6
00:00:15,815 --> 00:00:18,284
<i>Hyena, what do you think</i>

7
00:00:18,351 --> 00:00:19,919
about joining forces with me?

8
00:00:19,986 --> 00:00:22,822
<i>You want to avenge your dad, don't you?</i>

9
00:00:22,889 --> 00:00:25,158
<i>If two second-rates get together,</i>

10
00:00:25,225 --> 00:00:26,860
<i>our force still doubles.</i>

11
00:00:26,926 --> 00:00:31,464
<i>This moment marked the beginning</i>
<i>of a living hell.</i>

12
00:00:31,531 --> 00:00:35,702
<i>And I would end up being entrusted with</i>
<i>three wills.</i>

13
00:00:35,769 --> 00:00:37,570
<i>Just like a hyena,</i>

14
00:00:37,637 --> 00:00:39,773
<i>I can't help but trace the scent of death.</i>

15
00:00:40,340 --> 00:00:43,143
<i>This may be my fate</i>
<i>as an inheritance detective.</i>

16
00:00:43,209 --> 00:00:44,177
HAIE FAMILY GRAVE

17
00:00:46,646 --> 00:00:49,349
What is this "scoop"

18
00:00:49,416 --> 00:00:50,283
that you have?

19
00:00:51,418 --> 00:00:52,986
As if I'd tell you, fool.

20
00:00:53,553 --> 00:00:55,555
Answer my questions first.

21
00:00:56,723 --> 00:00:58,725
These are files

22
00:00:58,792 --> 00:01:01,861
on your father, Kazuhiro's Haie,
bus accident.

23
00:01:02,429 --> 00:01:05,397
I'll tell you what I found.

24
00:01:06,099 --> 00:01:08,468
If anything is wrong,
speak up and correct me.

25
00:01:10,637 --> 00:01:13,940
On December 15th, 2006,

26
00:01:14,007 --> 00:01:17,777
a temporary highway bus
fell and crashed in Minamiboso.

27
00:01:17,844 --> 00:01:19,646
<i>At first, everyone thought that</i>

28
00:01:19,712 --> 00:01:22,515
<i>the court would agree</i>
<i>with the defendant's claim</i>

29
00:01:22,582 --> 00:01:27,053
<i>that the driver, Mr. Kazuhiro Haie,</i>
<i>was not at fault,</i>

30
00:01:27,120 --> 00:01:29,889
<i>because that area was famous</i>
<i>for having strong winds.</i>

31
00:01:31,491 --> 00:01:32,826
However…

32
00:01:35,462 --> 00:01:36,763
the moment a newspaper article

33
00:01:36,830 --> 00:01:41,034
suggested that the driver
fell asleep at the wheel,

34
00:01:41,101 --> 00:01:43,937
the public was instantly stirred up

35
00:01:44,003 --> 00:01:46,639
and it even affected
the decision of the court.

36
00:01:46,706 --> 00:01:48,141
DEAD MEN TELL NO TALES

37
00:01:48,208 --> 00:01:50,944
In June 2008,

38
00:01:51,010 --> 00:01:53,680
the court found him guilty
of falling asleep at the wheel.

39
00:01:54,347 --> 00:01:55,882
It's an obvious misjudgment.

40
00:01:56,483 --> 00:02:00,420
That is why
Hyena just couldn't accept it,

41
00:02:00,487 --> 00:02:04,824
and asked a certain <i>chigyu</i> to verify it.

42
00:02:04,891 --> 00:02:06,993
How dare you call me a <i>chigyu.</i>

43
00:02:08,794 --> 00:02:10,964
You're Tomonaga, right?

44
00:02:13,366 --> 00:02:15,101
I read your blog.

45
00:02:15,635 --> 00:02:17,670
You investigate the truth behind

46
00:02:17,737 --> 00:02:20,540
all sorts of criminal cases using science.

47
00:02:20,607 --> 00:02:22,308
Honestly, I think you're a genius.

48
00:02:24,577 --> 00:02:25,612
Of course, I am.

49
00:02:26,179 --> 00:02:27,680
Will you cooperate with me?

50
00:02:31,918 --> 00:02:33,219
My dad was accused

51
00:02:33,286 --> 00:02:35,421
of falling asleep at the wheel
and I want to clear his name.

52
00:02:38,291 --> 00:02:39,526
BUS FELL IN MINAMIBOSO

53
00:02:39,592 --> 00:02:44,130
I can't just let them say,
"dead men tell no tales" and give up.

54
00:02:45,098 --> 00:02:46,633
This is the reason why

55
00:02:47,367 --> 00:02:48,668
I became a lawyer.

56
00:02:53,139 --> 00:02:56,409
Isn't this the reason why
you were fired from forensics?

57
00:03:00,980 --> 00:03:01,915
Listen,

58
00:03:01,981 --> 00:03:05,385
if he was asleep,
these skid marks wouldn't look like this.

59
00:03:05,451 --> 00:03:07,687
This is proof that Mr. Haie's father was

60
00:03:07,754 --> 00:03:09,689
trying to control the bus
against the wind.

61
00:03:10,623 --> 00:03:13,927
The results
from my reevaluation are flawless.

62
00:03:14,794 --> 00:03:18,598
It's absolutely unacceptable
to use science for injustice.

63
00:03:19,566 --> 00:03:23,269
This video proves that the judgment
was wrong.

64
00:03:23,836 --> 00:03:24,704
But

65
00:03:25,338 --> 00:03:27,774
this isn't enough to request

66
00:03:27,840 --> 00:03:29,375
a retrial.

67
00:03:29,442 --> 00:03:31,411
And more importantly,

68
00:03:31,477 --> 00:03:32,845
a retrial would mean suing

69
00:03:32,912 --> 00:03:35,248
the families of the people
who died in the accident.

70
00:03:35,315 --> 00:03:36,783
I can't do that.

71
00:03:37,650 --> 00:03:38,618
And so,

72
00:03:39,252 --> 00:03:41,354
that is why you and your mother

73
00:03:41,421 --> 00:03:45,225
are still paying 900 million yen
in compensation

74
00:03:45,291 --> 00:03:48,161
for the 30 victims who died.

75
00:03:50,163 --> 00:03:51,464
Why

76
00:03:52,298 --> 00:03:53,900
didn't you renounce inheritance?

77
00:03:56,002 --> 00:03:58,738
If you did,
you wouldn't have to pay anything.

78
00:04:01,674 --> 00:04:04,210
If you're trying to trick me,

79
00:04:04,777 --> 00:04:05,812
I won't forgive you.

80
00:04:06,546 --> 00:04:09,148
Whoa, that's a threat.
You can get arrested for that.

81
00:04:09,215 --> 00:04:10,917
Answer me!

82
00:04:14,587 --> 00:04:16,822
If I was trying to trick a fool,

83
00:04:16,889 --> 00:04:18,825
I wouldn't do it like this.

84
00:04:25,798 --> 00:04:26,866
My mother

85
00:04:28,434 --> 00:04:30,270
believed in my dad.

86
00:04:31,938 --> 00:04:35,341
So she had no doubt that
he would be found not liable.

87
00:04:36,242 --> 00:04:38,144
She thought that renouncing inheritance

88
00:04:39,879 --> 00:04:42,782
<i>would mean that we would be denying my dad</i>

89
00:04:42,849 --> 00:04:44,784
<i>and his dedication to his job.</i>

90
00:04:48,788 --> 00:04:50,156
But…

91
00:04:51,557 --> 00:04:54,994
your father was forced
to take the blame for everything…

92
00:05:00,633 --> 00:05:04,037
by the hands of a judge named Susuda.

93
00:05:07,974 --> 00:05:11,077
The one who pressured Susuda to do that

94
00:05:11,144 --> 00:05:13,079
is currently a Supreme Court justice.

95
00:05:15,682 --> 00:05:16,983
Kengo Jidori.

96
00:05:19,118 --> 00:05:21,487
If you look at this man's career,

97
00:05:21,554 --> 00:05:25,158
he has taken the fast track to success.

98
00:05:26,292 --> 00:05:29,662
During the trial in question,

99
00:05:29,729 --> 00:05:33,933
he was the Appointment Section chief of
the Supreme Court Personnel Affairs Bureau

100
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:38,304
and from there he became the director
of the Personnel Affairs Bureau and so on.

101
00:05:38,371 --> 00:05:41,708
He then went on to become
the President of the Tokyo High Court

102
00:05:41,774 --> 00:05:43,876
and a Supreme Court justice.

103
00:05:43,943 --> 00:05:48,681
There's no doubt that he is going to
become Chief Justice of the Supreme Court.

104
00:05:50,216 --> 00:05:52,985
Elites who have influence
in personnel affairs while they're young

105
00:05:53,052 --> 00:05:55,488
end up having the most power.

106
00:05:55,555 --> 00:05:57,423
According to my research,

107
00:05:57,490 --> 00:05:59,625
Jidori is the one who
"leaked" info to the media

108
00:05:59,692 --> 00:06:01,828
about your father
falling asleep at the wheel.

109
00:06:03,596 --> 00:06:04,697
I knew it.

110
00:06:04,764 --> 00:06:07,300
It takes a thief to catch a thief.

111
00:06:07,367 --> 00:06:10,269
Now, here is the part that I don't get.

112
00:06:12,538 --> 00:06:15,208
What does Jidori gain from bothering

113
00:06:15,274 --> 00:06:17,377
a poor family like the Haies?

114
00:06:18,010 --> 00:06:19,078
I've been

115
00:06:19,946 --> 00:06:23,082
thoroughly digging up dirt on Jidori,
that villain who is

116
00:06:23,149 --> 00:06:25,017
posing as a good guy.

117
00:06:25,952 --> 00:06:29,756
Besides you guys, everyone else
he's involved with are politicians.

118
00:06:30,757 --> 00:06:32,892
What in the world is the connection

119
00:06:32,959 --> 00:06:34,827
between you and Jidori?

120
00:06:39,132 --> 00:06:41,868
You resent Jidori too, right?

121
00:06:43,035 --> 00:06:44,804
Be honest with me.

122
00:06:45,371 --> 00:06:47,173
I'll help you.

123
00:06:47,240 --> 00:06:48,541
So when that's done,

124
00:06:49,809 --> 00:06:51,511
help me too.

125
00:06:58,751 --> 00:07:00,420
Kengo Jidori

126
00:07:02,755 --> 00:07:04,757
is my real father.

127
00:07:07,994 --> 00:07:08,995
What?

128
00:07:10,196 --> 00:07:11,297
My mother

129
00:07:12,165 --> 00:07:15,334
dated Jidori when they were in school.

130
00:07:16,235 --> 00:07:21,073
But Jidori
married a politician's daughter.

131
00:07:21,140 --> 00:07:24,877
That politician
was the then Minister of Finance

132
00:07:24,944 --> 00:07:27,513
<i>who later became Prime Minister,</i>

133
00:07:27,580 --> 00:07:28,815
<i>Shigemori Asaba.</i>

134
00:07:30,616 --> 00:07:32,552
My mother moved back in with her parents

135
00:07:33,553 --> 00:07:35,388
and gave birth to me all by herself.

136
00:07:36,322 --> 00:07:38,558
When I was three years old,

137
00:07:38,624 --> 00:07:40,393
she got married to

138
00:07:41,160 --> 00:07:42,528
<i>my late father.</i>

139
00:07:46,933 --> 00:07:49,335
I guess I was pretty dense.

140
00:07:50,403 --> 00:07:52,605
<i>I had no idea until…</i>

141
00:07:52,672 --> 00:07:53,506
NAME: NAO

142
00:07:53,573 --> 00:07:55,241
<i>…I saw the family register…</i>

143
00:07:55,308 --> 00:07:56,342
ADOPTIVE FATHER: KAZUHIRO HAIE
RELATIONSHIP: ADOPTED CHILD

144
00:07:56,409 --> 00:07:58,678
<i>…when doing my dad's</i>
<i>inheritance paperwork.</i>

145
00:07:59,445 --> 00:08:01,481
The fact that you didn't notice until then

146
00:08:03,616 --> 00:08:05,251
means he was a good dad.

147
00:08:06,886 --> 00:08:07,720
‪Yeah.‬

148
00:08:09,121 --> 00:08:11,724
When we went to Tokyo District Court
for the trial…

149
00:08:18,731 --> 00:08:23,102
My sincere condolences.

150
00:08:47,260 --> 00:08:48,661
That's him…

151
00:08:55,868 --> 00:08:57,169
When Jidori

152
00:08:58,638 --> 00:09:00,673
found out that I became a lawyer and was

153
00:09:00,740 --> 00:09:02,875
trying to prove my father's innocence,

154
00:09:03,809 --> 00:09:06,612
he falsely accused me of embezzling money.

155
00:09:07,480 --> 00:09:10,950
That embezzlement scandal that got you
shunned from the legal community?

156
00:09:11,017 --> 00:09:12,685
That was Jidori's trap too?

157
00:09:12,752 --> 00:09:13,786
That's right.

158
00:09:14,353 --> 00:09:17,323
I was processing a conservatorship
for an older wealthy individual

159
00:09:17,390 --> 00:09:19,759
when the family suddenly
accused me of embezzling.

160
00:09:19,825 --> 00:09:21,894
Unbeknownst to me, five million yen

161
00:09:21,961 --> 00:09:23,996
was wired to my personal bank account.

162
00:09:24,063 --> 00:09:26,732
I have no idea where this came from!

163
00:09:26,799 --> 00:09:28,868
You can't just make excuses like that

164
00:09:28,935 --> 00:09:30,536
when there's hard evidence.

165
00:09:31,938 --> 00:09:33,873
<i>I can't believe he'd go that far…</i>

166
00:09:35,942 --> 00:09:36,976
Even if

167
00:09:37,510 --> 00:09:39,412
I'm not a lawyer anymore,

168
00:09:40,680 --> 00:09:43,049
I want to settle the score for my dad,
no matter what.

169
00:09:44,850 --> 00:09:46,485
If I can't,

170
00:09:47,787 --> 00:09:49,889
what would I be living for?

171
00:09:55,261 --> 00:09:58,097
They say, "dead men tell no tales,"

172
00:09:59,065 --> 00:10:00,866
but science can tell their tales for them.

173
00:10:01,867 --> 00:10:04,070
The power of science
presents persuasive truths

174
00:10:04,737 --> 00:10:07,740
and proves their accuracy.

175
00:10:10,042 --> 00:10:13,446
I can't sit back and let them
bring shame on it like that.

176
00:10:16,682 --> 00:10:19,719
So that is <i>Chigyu's</i> raison d'être, huh?

177
00:10:20,286 --> 00:10:23,689
To use science
to help this foolish hyena's

178
00:10:23,756 --> 00:10:25,758
efforts to settle the score.

179
00:10:27,960 --> 00:10:29,061
And

180
00:10:30,029 --> 00:10:33,799
your mutual enemy is Jidori, right?

181
00:10:41,374 --> 00:10:43,776
This is getting interesting.

182
00:10:46,445 --> 00:10:49,849
First, we'll close in on Jidori
from the outside.

183
00:10:50,616 --> 00:10:53,285
We'll slowly strangle Jidori

184
00:10:53,352 --> 00:10:56,022
with fine silk threads.

185
00:11:02,261 --> 00:11:04,296
Let me use the bathroom.

186
00:11:21,447 --> 00:11:23,249
<i>Unless you start treatment right away,</i>

187
00:11:23,315 --> 00:11:26,686
you might only have three months to live.

188
00:11:32,892 --> 00:11:34,627
Come on…

189
00:11:35,227 --> 00:11:36,762
We're just getting started.

190
00:11:37,697 --> 00:11:39,532
Come on, my body…

191
00:11:43,402 --> 00:11:45,671
That was a huge one!

192
00:11:48,874 --> 00:11:52,111
We'll go after this guy.

193
00:11:52,812 --> 00:11:56,749
The judge for the first trial
Komei Susuda.

194
00:11:57,316 --> 00:11:59,719
He's still in his fifties,

195
00:11:59,785 --> 00:12:02,722
but he retired a year ago
and is living a leisurely life.

196
00:12:02,788 --> 00:12:04,256
You located him?

197
00:12:04,323 --> 00:12:06,058
Even I couldn't find him.

198
00:12:06,125 --> 00:12:08,794
Like you said,
it takes a thief to catch a thief.

199
00:12:11,897 --> 00:12:13,966
Doesn't seem like a leisurely life.

200
00:12:14,033 --> 00:12:16,202
He willingly retired because he either

201
00:12:16,268 --> 00:12:18,104
was fed up with Jidori

202
00:12:18,704 --> 00:12:20,206
or because he's being threatened.

203
00:12:20,272 --> 00:12:23,042
He might be trembling out of fear
on the inside.

204
00:12:23,943 --> 00:12:26,378
If we target him, even a hyena…

205
00:12:26,445 --> 00:12:27,279
‪That's right.‬

206
00:12:28,347 --> 00:12:29,448
I can fight.

207
00:12:42,228 --> 00:12:44,563
So bitter! What the heck!

208
00:12:59,044 --> 00:13:01,947
I am going to publish a huge scoop soon.

209
00:13:02,014 --> 00:13:04,950
I have already
lived through that hell once.

210
00:13:05,017 --> 00:13:07,253
You'll be ousted from the media.

211
00:13:07,319 --> 00:13:08,621
Make sure you give me

212
00:13:09,188 --> 00:13:10,923
<i>updates on Hyena.</i>

213
00:13:10,990 --> 00:13:12,191
SEBUMI LAW OFFICE

214
00:13:12,258 --> 00:13:13,993
-Thank you for your work.
-Thank you.

215
00:13:16,896 --> 00:13:18,297
Excuse me.

216
00:13:22,835 --> 00:13:24,370
Attorney Fukushi,

217
00:13:24,870 --> 00:13:29,642
you recruited me
in order to protect me, right?

218
00:13:32,278 --> 00:13:34,814
I heard that punk named Haie

219
00:13:36,315 --> 00:13:39,151
has an assistant named Mitomi.

220
00:13:42,221 --> 00:13:44,056
Will you please

221
00:13:45,524 --> 00:13:47,259
protect Sensei as well?

222
00:13:49,862 --> 00:13:53,833
There's probably nothing that I can do.

223
00:13:54,900 --> 00:13:58,771
I'm sure that is why you
told me to come here.

224
00:14:00,773 --> 00:14:01,640
But…

225
00:14:04,076 --> 00:14:06,445
you are different.

226
00:14:09,615 --> 00:14:11,050
Please…

227
00:14:11,116 --> 00:14:12,985
Please help Sensei.

228
00:14:16,622 --> 00:14:19,158
For you, Ms. Reiko, I will.

229
00:14:23,395 --> 00:14:25,130
Thank you very much.

230
00:14:46,819 --> 00:14:47,686
Let go!

231
00:14:49,788 --> 00:14:51,457
Who are you?

232
00:14:51,523 --> 00:14:52,858
KAORU HAGETA

233
00:14:52,925 --> 00:14:56,595
I am going to publish a huge scoop soon.

234
00:14:57,596 --> 00:14:59,632
In order to reform the Supreme Court

235
00:14:59,698 --> 00:15:03,068
which controls
this country's judicial system.

236
00:15:03,636 --> 00:15:05,371
I'll mention your name too.

237
00:15:05,437 --> 00:15:06,872
FORMER JUDGE
KOMEI SUSUDA

238
00:15:06,939 --> 00:15:08,507
That's why

239
00:15:08,574 --> 00:15:12,511
I politely came here to introduce myself.

240
00:15:14,280 --> 00:15:17,182
Well then, what do you think the scoop is?

241
00:15:18,350 --> 00:15:19,718
Hint number one:

242
00:15:20,486 --> 00:15:23,489
I'll also mention the names
of people who live in Nagatacho.

243
00:15:24,056 --> 00:15:25,591
Hint number two:

244
00:15:26,492 --> 00:15:29,628
I'll also mention a judge whose name
starts with the letter J.

245
00:15:31,630 --> 00:15:35,134
Since he's a judge,
I guess we'll call him J.J.

246
00:15:39,438 --> 00:15:43,142
Well, enough about the scoop.
I have something else

247
00:15:43,709 --> 00:15:45,110
I want to ask you.

248
00:15:47,379 --> 00:15:49,214
It's about this written judgment.

249
00:15:49,782 --> 00:15:53,285
"Although evidence such as tachograph data
was submitted,

250
00:15:54,153 --> 00:15:57,623
such evidence was
one-sidedly produced by the defendant

251
00:15:58,290 --> 00:16:00,693
and holds no credibility whatsoever."

252
00:16:01,627 --> 00:16:03,829
It is not conclusive enough to prove that

253
00:16:03,896 --> 00:16:06,332
the driver
did not fall asleep at the wheel."

254
00:16:06,899 --> 00:16:08,133
That's what it says.

255
00:16:08,867 --> 00:16:10,602
It's impressive how you can

256
00:16:10,669 --> 00:16:12,805
string words together just to make

257
00:16:12,871 --> 00:16:14,873
something white seem like it's black.

258
00:16:16,108 --> 00:16:16,942
Tell me,

