I have no intention of working under

515
00:32:05,290 --> 00:32:08,259
a man who is a coward. Bye!

516
00:32:10,862 --> 00:32:12,030
Ms. Reiko…

517
00:32:16,534 --> 00:32:19,971
Come on, quickly tell me what's going on.

518
00:32:20,038 --> 00:32:23,274
I'm telling you
that I don't know anything.

519
00:32:23,341 --> 00:32:25,643
More like, I'm going to tell on you
to Mr. Haie.

520
00:32:25,710 --> 00:32:29,580
Come on, don't say that!
Please, please, tell me

521
00:32:29,647 --> 00:32:32,417
what Sensei is trying to do right now.

522
00:32:36,487 --> 00:32:37,822
Fine.

523
00:32:39,290 --> 00:32:42,160
These are my gym customers.
I'll plan three mixers with them.

524
00:32:42,226 --> 00:32:44,262
-All right.
-That was fast.

525
00:32:44,329 --> 00:32:47,298
So basically, in the end,

526
00:32:47,365 --> 00:32:50,568
unless we get Susuda's testimony…

527
00:32:50,635 --> 00:32:52,704
SUSUDA
WANT A TESTIMONY

528
00:32:52,770 --> 00:32:53,938
…we can't win…

529
00:32:54,005 --> 00:32:55,707
I WAS PRESSURED

530
00:32:55,773 --> 00:32:58,843
…even if we sue the state.

531
00:33:01,412 --> 00:33:03,548
-You owe me three mixers.
-I know.

532
00:33:04,515 --> 00:33:05,783
Thank you very much.

533
00:33:07,819 --> 00:33:09,654
You perverted science jerk.

534
00:33:11,456 --> 00:33:12,557
Ms. Reiko.

535
00:33:14,359 --> 00:33:15,560
Be careful.

536
00:33:16,294 --> 00:33:19,597
I know. I'm just going to
look into Mr. Susuda.

537
00:33:40,318 --> 00:33:41,352
Hello.

538
00:33:42,320 --> 00:33:43,521
<i>It's me.</i>

539
00:33:52,363 --> 00:33:53,998
Who is this?

540
00:33:54,766 --> 00:33:56,367
The two of us should meet.

541
00:33:57,802 --> 00:33:59,504
Kaneueda at eight o'clock.

542
00:34:00,605 --> 00:34:02,473
They'll know once you get there.

543
00:34:24,062 --> 00:34:25,897
What are you scheming?

544
00:34:27,431 --> 00:34:28,666
What is it for?

545
00:34:29,833 --> 00:34:33,371
To reveal the truth
about Dad's bus accident

546
00:34:33,438 --> 00:34:35,339
and settle the score.

547
00:34:36,107 --> 00:34:37,275
And

548
00:34:38,309 --> 00:34:40,545
to expose your evil deeds.

549
00:34:41,545 --> 00:34:45,149
How you're trying to become
Chief Justice of the Supreme Court,

550
00:34:45,216 --> 00:34:49,020
a position that gets paid just as much
as the Prime Minister,

551
00:34:49,087 --> 00:34:51,089
but in reality, you're a lowlife villain

552
00:34:51,155 --> 00:34:53,257
who twists the truth.

553
00:34:54,859 --> 00:34:56,960
That should be easy then.

554
00:34:58,763 --> 00:35:01,499
"I am Jidori's son.

555
00:35:02,433 --> 00:35:04,402
My biological father

556
00:35:04,936 --> 00:35:06,704
tried to deprive

557
00:35:07,472 --> 00:35:09,440
my mother, me, and my adoptive father

558
00:35:09,507 --> 00:35:11,709
of our happiness."

559
00:35:12,944 --> 00:35:15,346
That's all you have to say

560
00:35:16,380 --> 00:35:19,050
with tears in your eyes.

561
00:35:30,995 --> 00:35:33,431
My friend told me the same thing

562
00:35:33,498 --> 00:35:34,732
and laughed.

563
00:35:36,567 --> 00:35:38,102
We are

564
00:35:38,669 --> 00:35:40,771
trying to break the system of this country

565
00:35:40,838 --> 00:35:44,208
that's being run by people
you gave power to.

566
00:35:45,443 --> 00:35:48,045
The separation of powers
is a complete sham

567
00:35:48,679 --> 00:35:50,248
and we say, "To hell with that."

568
00:36:03,928 --> 00:36:05,329
Wonderful.

569
00:36:06,264 --> 00:36:07,365
Go ahead and try.

570
00:36:08,266 --> 00:36:10,968
It's like a kid playing pretend war.

571
00:36:16,007 --> 00:36:17,408
However,

572
00:36:18,876 --> 00:36:24,515
you should worry about the safety
of your friends.

573
00:36:25,082 --> 00:36:26,884
Kaoru Hageta,

574
00:36:28,219 --> 00:36:32,323
a freelance journalist who was fired
from Kyojo Tsushin.

575
00:36:33,257 --> 00:36:37,495
I hear he's been hanging out
at your office since eight days ago.

576
00:36:39,397 --> 00:36:41,999
Hideki Tomonaga is a capable scientist,

577
00:36:42,066 --> 00:36:45,803
but I wonder why he left
the forensics department?

578
00:36:47,471 --> 00:36:50,942
Japan is a dangerous place these days.

579
00:36:54,579 --> 00:36:56,514
Many accidents happen as well.

580
00:36:58,716 --> 00:37:00,818
What I'm trying to say is,

581
00:37:02,653 --> 00:37:04,922
that you shouldn't let

582
00:37:06,958 --> 00:37:09,860
your nonsense put your close friends

583
00:37:09,927 --> 00:37:14,465
in harm's way, that's all.

584
00:37:17,535 --> 00:37:20,271
I'll excuse myself now.

585
00:37:23,708 --> 00:37:25,610
I'm glad we got to meet.

586
00:37:26,410 --> 00:37:27,645
I know

587
00:37:28,479 --> 00:37:31,282
very well now, that you are just like

588
00:37:32,116 --> 00:37:37,355
the father who raised you,
and you can only think of trivial things.

589
00:38:01,812 --> 00:38:03,047
How was it?

590
00:38:03,114 --> 00:38:04,982
He threatened me like crazy.

591
00:38:05,049 --> 00:38:07,551
He told me to treasure my friends.

592
00:38:07,618 --> 00:38:09,487
It proves that Jidori is panicking.

593
00:38:10,888 --> 00:38:12,456
It's finally happening.

594
00:38:13,157 --> 00:38:13,991
‪Yeah.‬

595
00:38:16,160 --> 00:38:18,562
Both you and Tomonaga should be careful.

596
00:38:20,031 --> 00:38:22,933
Also, it's unlikely,

597
00:38:24,101 --> 00:38:26,337
but if anything happens to me,

598
00:38:26,937 --> 00:38:28,506
I'll leave the rest to you.

599
00:38:34,111 --> 00:38:35,946
I will protect you.

600
00:38:39,083 --> 00:38:40,484
Thank you.

601
00:38:40,985 --> 00:38:42,987
I'll need 2,500 yen per hour.

602
00:38:47,291 --> 00:38:48,392
Haie.

603
00:38:54,498 --> 00:38:55,966
I'm sorry

604
00:38:57,335 --> 00:38:58,636
about everything.

605
00:39:08,646 --> 00:39:10,314
It'll be 500 yen per hour.

606
00:39:42,913 --> 00:39:44,315
Excuse me.

607
00:39:59,730 --> 00:40:01,766
Be quiet. Don't move.

608
00:40:02,333 --> 00:40:05,069
My mind is already set
so I have nothing to fear.

609
00:40:08,139 --> 00:40:10,007
You'll have to make up your mind too.

610
00:40:10,074 --> 00:40:11,776
I'm a woman ready to risk my life.

611
00:40:18,382 --> 00:40:19,517
A will?

612
00:40:27,191 --> 00:40:30,461
<i>They found damning photographs</i>
<i>regarding Daiya Asaba's case.</i>

613
00:40:30,528 --> 00:40:32,029
<i>I'm going to go check now.</i>

614
00:40:32,963 --> 00:40:35,232
Why is he sending me the address?

615
00:40:36,200 --> 00:40:38,068
COFFEE BEANS

616
00:40:39,103 --> 00:40:41,539
It seems the time has finally come,

617
00:40:41,605 --> 00:40:42,706
Dad.

618
00:40:47,311 --> 00:40:49,513
HIDEKI TOMONAGA

619
00:40:50,548 --> 00:40:53,684
-What's up?
-I got a strange email from Mr. Hage.

620
00:40:54,852 --> 00:40:55,820
<i>Haie.</i>

621
00:40:56,353 --> 00:40:57,955
<i>If anything happens to me,</i>

622
00:40:58,889 --> 00:40:59,990
<i>I'll leave the rest to you.</i>

623
00:41:13,070 --> 00:41:14,672
I'm heading to that address now.

624
00:41:15,239 --> 00:41:16,340
What's going on?

625
00:41:16,907 --> 00:41:19,410
I have a bad feeling about this.

626
00:41:33,557 --> 00:41:35,726
Come on, come on…

627
00:41:35,793 --> 00:41:39,196
Let me get to a place
where there's nobody around.

628
00:41:45,936 --> 00:41:47,638
WILL

629
00:41:47,705 --> 00:41:49,507
Will you please

630
00:41:50,074 --> 00:41:52,243
tell the truth during the trial?

631
00:41:53,444 --> 00:41:56,046
If you don't promise me that,

632
00:41:57,181 --> 00:41:58,382
I'll have to…

633
00:42:02,419 --> 00:42:03,754
What are you doing?

634
00:42:03,821 --> 00:42:05,489
Ms. Reiko,

635
00:42:05,556 --> 00:42:07,291
why aren't you picking up?

636
00:42:09,994 --> 00:42:11,562
I'm such a fool.

637
00:42:15,065 --> 00:42:16,066
<i>I will</i>

638
00:42:16,634 --> 00:42:18,235
die right here.

639
00:42:18,302 --> 00:42:20,604
Hey, stop!

640
00:42:20,671 --> 00:42:21,939
Stop it!

641
00:42:29,747 --> 00:42:32,750
This might be enough to turn the tables.

642
00:43:24,969 --> 00:43:26,637
WILL

643
00:43:39,717 --> 00:43:40,951
EXPRESS DELIVERY

644
00:43:41,018 --> 00:43:43,253
Mr. Haie, you have an express delivery.

645
00:44:01,071 --> 00:44:03,007
WILL

646
00:44:03,073 --> 00:44:05,009
KAORU HAGETA

647
00:44:10,381 --> 00:44:12,282
-All by yourself…
-Find it!

648
00:44:12,349 --> 00:44:13,484
<i>It's my battle as well.</i>

649
00:44:13,550 --> 00:44:14,918
<i>Stay away from me.</i>

650
00:44:14,985 --> 00:44:15,953
Subtitle translation by: Kiko Morita
